'''Florian Richard Wirtz''' ({{IPA|de|ˈfloːriːˌɑːn ˈvɪɾt͡s}}; born 3 May 2003) is a German professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] or [[left midfielder]] for {{English football updater|Liverpoo}} club [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] and the [[Germany national football team|Germany national team]]. He is widely regarded as one of the best attacking midfielders in the world.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-06-04 |title=2025 FC 100: Bellingham among best attacking midfielders in men's soccer |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/45178766/2025-fc-100-bellingham-best-attacking-midfielders-mens-soccer |access-date=2025-08-04 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Ford |first=Matt |date=2025-06-20 |title=Record-breaker Wirtz's journey to Liverpool |url=https://www.premierleague.com/en/news/4324665 |access-date=2025-08-04 |website=Premier League |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=White |first=Mark |date=26 February 2025 |title=Ranked! The 10 best attacking midfielders in the world |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/ranked-the-10-best-attacking-midfielders-in-the-world-right-now |access-date=25 May 2025 |website=[[FourFourTwo]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-07-22 |title=The 25 Best Attacking Midfielders in World Soccer: Ranked |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/the-best-attacking-midfielders-in-world-soccer-ranked |access-date=2025-08-04 |website=SI |language=en-US}}</ref>

Wirtz rose through the youth system at [[1. FC Köln]] before moving to [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]] in 2020. He made his first team debut at the age of 17, becoming the youngest scorer in [[Bundesliga]] history.<ref name="g630">{{cite web | title=The top 10 youngest goalscorers in Bundesliga history | website=Bundesliga | date=2022-09-11 | url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/the-top-10-youngest-goalscorers-in-bundesliga-history-pulisic-werner-havertz-11128 | access-date=2025-09-12}}</ref> He played a pivotal role in Leverkusen's [[2023–24 Bayer 04 Leverkusen season|unbeaten domestic double in the 2023–24 season]], earning Bundesliga Player of the Season honours and recording 18 goals in 49 appearances.<ref name=":2">{{Cite news |date=2025-06-20 |title=Liverpool shatter club transfer record to sign Germany midfielder Wirtz |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/liverpool-shatter-club-transfer-record-sign-germany-midfielder-wirtz-2025-06-20/ |access-date=2025-08-01 |work=Reuters |language=en}}</ref> In June 2025, Wirtz transferred to [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] for a club-record fee (approximately £100 million plus bonuses), breaking the previous Premier League record for the most expensive transfer and marking a high‑profile move in his emerging career.<ref name=":2" />

Internationally, Wirtz debuted for Germany in September 2021 after representing the country at various youth levels. He later became the youngest ever goalscorer for [[Germany national football team|Germany]] in the history of the [[UEFA European Championship|European Championships]] after he scored a goal against [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]] at [[UEFA Euro 2024]].

== Early life ==
Wirtz was born on 3 May 2003 in the [[Brauweiler]] district of [[Pulheim]], [[North Rhine-Westphalia]].<ref name="WF">{{WorldFootball.net}}</ref>

== Club career ==
=== Early career ===
Regarded as a big talent in German football, Wirtz joined the youth team of [[1. FC Köln]] in 2010, where he remained until he was signed by [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]] in January 2020.<ref name="Wonderkid">{{cite news |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/who-is-florian-wirtz-bayer-leverkusen-s-wonderkid-youngest-ever-debutant-11192 |title=Florian Wirtz: Who is Bayer Leverkusen's new wonderkid and youngest-ever debutant? |work=Bundesliga |date=22 May 2020 |access-date=5 March 2021 |archive-date=9 September 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210909191000/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/who-is-florian-wirtz-bayer-leverkusen-s-wonderkid-youngest-ever-debutant-11192 |url-status=live}}</ref> His transfer to Leverkusen was controversial, as Köln felt that Leverkusen violated a gentleman's agreement between the two clubs in signing Wirtz.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Florian Wirtz, the Cologne gem shining in Leverkusen |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/why-florian-wirtz-left-cologne-for-bayer-leverkusen-24987 |access-date=20 May 2024 |website=bundesliga.com – the official Bundesliga website |language=en |archive-date=9 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240609165908/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/why-florian-wirtz-left-cologne-for-bayer-leverkusen-24987 |url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Bayer Leverkusen ===
==== 2020: Professional debut ====
After impressing for the under-17 team, Wirtz made his senior professional debut for Leverkusen in the [[Bundesliga]] on 18 May 2020, starting in an away match against [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/match-report/ma8936187/lineup/ |title=Germany " Bundesliga 2019/2020 " 26. Round " Werder Bremen – Bayer Leverkusen |website=WorldFootball.net |date=18 May 2020 |access-date=18 May 2020 |archive-date=28 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210828155327/https://www.worldfootball.net/report/bundesliga-2019-2020-werder-bremen-bayer-leverkusen/ |url-status=live}}</ref> In doing so, he overtook [[Kai Havertz]] as Leverkusen's youngest player in the league, at the age of 17 years and 15 days.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/florian-wirtz-replaces-kai-havertz-bayer-leverkusen-s-youngest-ever-player-11142 |title=Florian Wirtz replaces Kai Havertz as Bayer Leverkusen's youngest ever player |website=[[Bundesliga]] |publisher=[[Deutsche Fußball Liga]] |date=18 May 2020 |access-date=18 May 2020 |archive-date=30 July 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200730113852/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/florian-wirtz-replaces-kai-havertz-bayer-leverkusen-s-youngest-ever-player-11142 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 6 June, Wirtz scored his first goal for Leverkusen in the 89th minute of their 4–2 home loss against [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]], making Wirtz the youngest goalscorer in Bundesliga history at the age of 17 years and 34 days.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.kicker.de/leverkusen-gegen-bayern-2020-bundesliga-4588921/analyse |title=Auch Leverkusen kein Hindernis: Bayern marschiert weiter zum Titel |trans-title=Leverkusen no hindrance either: Bayern marches on to the title |work=[[Kicker (sports magazine)|kicker]] |date=6 June 2020 |access-date=6 June 2020 |language=de |archive-date=4 October 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211004220103/https://www.kicker.de/leverkusen-gegen-bayern-2020-bundesliga-4588921/analyse |url-status=live}}</ref> This record would later be surpassed by [[Youssoufa Moukoko]] less than a year later, aged 16 years and 28 days.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/youssoufa-moukoko-youngest-goalscorer-in-history-at-16-borussia-dortmund-14000 |title=Youssoufa Moukoko becomes youngest ever Bundesliga scorer for Borussia Dortmund against Union Berlin |work=Bundesliga |date=18 December 2020 |access-date=18 December 2020 |archive-date=17 September 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210917073658/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/youssoufa-moukoko-youngest-goalscorer-in-history-at-16-borussia-dortmund-14000 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 22 October, he scored his first goal in European competitions in a 6–2 win over [[OGC Nice|Nice]] during the [[2020–21 UEFA Europa League|2020–21 Europa League]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.tagesspiegel.de/sport/bayer-leverkusen-startet-mit-kantersieg-4205380.html |title=6:2 gegen Nizza in der Europa League: Bayer Leverkusen startet mit Kantersieg |work=Der Tagesspiegel |language=de |date=22 October 2020 |access-date=27 October 2023 |archive-date=27 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231027120617/https://www.tagesspiegel.de/sport/bayer-leverkusen-startet-mit-kantersieg-4205380.html |url-status=live}}</ref>

==== 2020–23: Contract extension and long-term injury ====
Wirtz signed a contract extension with the club on 23 December 2020, extending his deal until 2023.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bayer04.de/en-us/news/bayer04/florian-wirtz-extends-contract-to-2023 |title=Florian Wirtz extends contract to 2023 |publisher=Bayer 04 Leverkusen |date=23 December 2020 |access-date=5 March 2021 |archive-date=31 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210831001956/https://www.bayer04.de/en-us/news/bayer04/florian-wirtz-extends-contract-to-2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 19 January 2021, he scored the winner in the 80th minute of Leverkusen's 2–1 home victory over [[Borussia Dortmund]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/bayer-leverkusen-borussia-dortmund-live-line-ups-stats-haaland-reyna-sancho-14356 |title=Florian Wirtz fires Bayer Leverkusen back to winning ways against Borussia Dortmund |work=Bundesliga |date=19 January 2021 |access-date=19 January 2021 |archive-date=9 September 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210909190824/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/bayer-leverkusen-borussia-dortmund-live-line-ups-stats-haaland-reyna-sancho-14356 |url-status=live}}</ref> Wirtz scored his fifth career Bundesliga goal in a 5–2 win against [[VfB Stuttgart]] on 6 February, becoming the first player in league history to reach this benchmark before turning eighteen years old.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/florian-wirtz-continues-to-rewrite-history-for-bayer-leverkusen-moukoko-14665 |title=Florian Wirtz continues to rewrite Bundesliga history for Bayer Leverkusen |work=Bundesliga |date=6 February 2021 |access-date=5 March 2021 |archive-date=29 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210829065711/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/florian-wirtz-continues-to-rewrite-history-for-bayer-leverkusen-moukoko-14665 |url-status=live}}</ref> He extended his contract until 2026 on 3 May 2021, the day of his 18th birthday.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bayer04.de/en-us/news/bayer04/bayer-04-extend-florian-wirtz-contract-to-2026 |title=Bayer 04 extend Florian Wirtz contract to 2026 |publisher=Bayer 04 Leverkusen |date=3 May 2021 |access-date=3 May 2021 |archive-date=7 December 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211207131742/https://www.bayer04.de/en-us/news/bayer04/bayer-04-extend-florian-wirtz-contract-to-2026 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 28 November 2021, Wirtz netted his fifth Bundesliga goal of the season in a 3–1 win against [[RB Leipzig]] to become the first player under the age of 19 to score more than ten Bundesliga goals.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/bayer-leverkusen-florian-wirtz-history-scoring-record-leipzig-u19-10-goals-18040 |title=Bayer Leverkusen's Florian Wirtz sets new Bundesliga scoring record |work=Bundesliga |date=29 November 2021 |access-date=29 November 2021 |archive-date=30 November 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211130060235/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/bayer-leverkusen-florian-wirtz-history-scoring-record-leipzig-u19-10-goals-18040 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 15 December, in a match against [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|TSG Hoffenheim]], he became the youngest player to reach 50 Bundesliga appearances at the age of 18 years and 223 days.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/florian-wirtz-becomes-youngest-player-to-make-50-bundesliga-appearances-18236 |title=Florian Wirtz becomes youngest player to make 50 Bundesliga appearances |work=Bundesliga |date=15 December 2021 |access-date=15 December 2021 |archive-date=15 December 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211215231810/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/florian-wirtz-becomes-youngest-player-to-make-50-bundesliga-appearances-18236 |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 13 March 2022, Wirtz tore his [[anterior cruciate ligament]] in a 1–0 defeat against 1. FC Köln, resulting in him missing the rest of the [[2021–22 Bundesliga]] season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dw.com/en/florian-wirtz-out-for-the-season-after-acl-injury/a-61112916 |title=Florian Wirtz out for the season after ACL injury |website=DW |date=13 March 2022 |access-date=17 April 2022 |archive-date=13 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220313190636/https://www.dw.com/en/florian-wirtz-out-for-the-season-after-acl-injury/a-61112916 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 22 January 2023, he played his first competitive match in ten months, coming off the bench in a 3–2 away win over [[Borussia Mönchengladbach]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.spox.com/de/sport/fussball/bundesliga/2301/Artikel/borussia-moenchengladbach-vs-bayer-leverkusen-bundesliga-heute-im-liveticker.html |title=Bundesliga, Borussia Mönchengladbach vs. Bayer Leverkusen: Das 2:3 im Liveticker zum Nachlesen |publisher=spox.com |language=de |date=22 January 2023 |access-date=27 October 2023 |archive-date=27 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231027120621/https://www.spox.com/de/sport/fussball/bundesliga/2301/Artikel/borussia-moenchengladbach-vs-bayer-leverkusen-bundesliga-heute-im-liveticker.html |url-status=live}}</ref>

==== 2023–24: Domestic double and player of the season award ====
[[File:Florian Wirtz 2024.jpg|thumb|Wirtz taking a penalty in a UEFA Champions League game against Red Bull Salzburg in November 2024.]]
On 26 October 2023, he scored a goal and provided a hat-trick of assists in a 5–1 victory over [[Qarabağ FK|Qarabağ]] during the [[2023–24 UEFA Europa League|2023–24 Europa League]] group stage.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kicker.de/leverkusen-gegen-qarabag-2023-europa-league-4890544/analyse |title=Wirtz wirbelt nach Belieben: Bayer lässt Qarabag keine Chance |publisher=Kicker |language=de |date=26 October 2023 |access-date=27 October 2023 |archive-date=27 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231027120617/https://www.kicker.de/leverkusen-gegen-qarabag-2023-europa-league-4890544/spielbericht |url-status=live}}</ref> On 14 April 2024, Wirtz scored his first career hat-trick, leading his team to a historic 5–0 title-clinching win over [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]], which gave Bayer their first [[Deutsche Meister|German championship]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/bayer-leverkusen-werder-bremen-xabi-alonso-champions-title-free-highlights-26914 |title=Bayer Leverkusen beat Werder Bremen to win the Bundesliga! |publisher=Bundesliga |date=14 April 2024 |access-date=14 April 2024 |archive-date=14 April 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240414221954/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/bayer-leverkusen-werder-bremen-xabi-alonso-champions-title-free-highlights-26914 |url-status=live}}</ref> By the end of the season, he would win the [[2024 DFB-Pokal final|DFB-Pokal final]] following a 1–0 victory over [[1. FC Kaiserslautern|Kaiserslautern]] as well as reach the [[2024 UEFA Europa League final|final]] of the [[2023–24 UEFA Europa League|UEFA Europa League]]. With twenty-two goal involvements throughout the season for his club in Bundesliga, he was voted player of the season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bayer04.de/en-us/news/bayer04/florian-wirtz-voted-bundesliga-player-of-the-season-202324 |title=Florian Wirtz voted Bundesliga Player of the Season 2023/24 |publisher=Bayer 04 Leverkusen |date=20 May 2024 }}</ref>

==== 2024–25: DFL-Supercup title, Champions League debut and departure ====
In the beginning of the [[2024–25 Bundesliga|2024–25 season]], Wirtz would win the [[2024 DFL-Supercup|DFL-Supercup]] with his team against [[VfB Stuttgart]] on penalties.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/bayer-leverkusen-vfb-stuttgart-supercup-preview-live-blog-report-alonso-28479 |title=Bayer Leverkusen battle back to beat VfB Stuttgart on penalties in Supercup |publisher=Bundesliga |date=17 August 2024 }}</ref> He made his [[UEFA Champions League]] debut on the first matchday in a 4–0 away victory over [[Feyenoord]], in which he scored a first-half brace and was named [[Player of the match|man of the match]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/720430 |title=Wirtz double helps Leverkusen rout Feyenoord to start UCL |publisher=ESPN |date=19 September 2024 }}</ref> Wirtz would go on to achieve this honour in four further matches against [[AC Milan]], [[Stade Brestois 29|Brest]], [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]] and [[AC Sparta Prague|Sparta Prague]], three of which he scored in; his five man of the match awards was more than any other player that [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League|season]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0291-1be11d1a20a2-9d5d04b25766-1000--every-uefa-champions-league-player-of-the-match/ |title=Every UEFA Champions League Player of the Match |publisher=UEFA |date=31 May 2025 }}</ref> He also became the first German player to score five goals in five Champions League matches.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/florian-wirtz-shining-light-guiding-the-way-at-bayer-leverkusen-new-contract-30120 |title=Florian Wirtz: The shining light guiding the way at Bayer Leverkusen |publisher=Bundesliga |date=17 December 2024 }}</ref> His side would eventually be knocked out in the round of 16 by fellow Bundesliga side Bayern Munich 5–0 on aggregate, of which he missed the second leg match due to injury.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kicker.de/leverkusen-gegen-bayern-2025-champions-league-5015522/analyse |title=Kane zieht Leverkusen den Stecker: Bayerns Traum vom "Finale dahoam" lebt weiter |publisher=Kicker |language=de |date=11 March 2025 }}</ref>

===Liverpool===
[[File:Florian Wirtz 04012026 (3) (extracted).jpg|thumb|right|Wirtz with [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] in 2026]]
On 20 June 2025, Wirtz joined [[Premier League]] club [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] on a long-term contract for a reported fee of depending on the source £100&nbsp;million (€117.5&nbsp;million) or £107&nbsp;million (€125&nbsp;million), with £16&nbsp;million (€18.8&nbsp;million) or €25&nbsp;million in bonuses.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Ornstein |first=David |date=13 June 2025 |title=Liverpool agree €136.3m transfer of Florian Wirtz from Leverkusen |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6410031/2025/06/13/liverpool-transfer-wirtz-transfer-latest/ |access-date=13 June 2025 |publisher=[[The Athletic]] }}</ref><ref name=":1" /> Wirtz became the sixth most expensive footballer of all time, and also became the largest transfer in the history of the [[Bundesliga]], replacing [[Ousmane Dembélé]] as record holder.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web |date=2025-06-20 |title=Rekord-Deal perfekt: Wirtz wechselt nach Liverpool |url=https://www.kicker.de/rekord-deal-perfekt-wirtz-wechselt-nach-liverpool-1122706/artikel |access-date=2025-06-20 |website=kicker |language=de}}</ref> His transfer represented a club record fee for Liverpool, succeeding [[Darwin Núñez]]'s move from [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] in 2022, as well as a potential [[Progression of the British football transfer fee record|British record transfer]], should the add-ons be activated.<ref>{{Cite web |date=20 June 2025 |title=Florian Wirtz seals Liverpool move from Bayer Leverkusen in club record £116m deal |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2025/jun/20/florian-wirtz-liverpool-bayer-leverkusen-club-record-116m-deal |access-date=20 June 2025 |publisher=[[The Guardian]] }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Joyce |first=Paul |title=Florian Wirtz: How Liverpool won the battle for German starlet |url=https://www.thetimes.com/sport/football/article/florian-wirtz-liverpool-bayer-leverkusen-6r0kq937n |access-date=20 June 2025 |work=The Times |date=13 June 2025}}</ref>

Wirtz made his debut for Liverpool on 10 August in the [[2025 FA Community Shield|FA Community Shield]] against [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]], recording an assist in a 2–2 draw in normal time, though his side would eventually lose 3–2 on [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalties]].<ref>{{cite news |date=10 August 2025 |title=Crystal Palace 2–2 Liverpool (3–2 on pens) |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cy7y0p1p7ezt |access-date=11 August 2025 |publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> On 15 August, he made his league debut for Liverpool in a late 4–2 win over [[AFC Bournemouth|Bournemouth]].<ref>{{cite news |last=McNulty |first=Phil |date=15 August 2025 |title=Liverpool 4–2 Bournemouth: Champions score twice to win Premier League opener |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/ce833z5j7yzt |access-date=16 August 2025 |publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> Later that year, on 22 October, he provided his first two assists in a 5–1 away victory over [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] in the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Rose |first=Gary |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cx2ny502krkt |title=Eintracht Frankfurt 1–5 Liverpool |publisher=BBC Sport |date=22 October 2025 }}</ref> Two months later, on 20 December, he recorded his first Premier League assist in a 2–1 away win over [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Urquhart |first=Joe |url=https://www.liverpoolfc.com/news/florian-wirtz-victory-tottenham-three-points-are-what-count |title=Florian Wirtz on victory at Tottenham: 'Three points are what count' |publisher=Liverpool F.C. |date=21 December 2025 }}</ref> A week later, on 27 December, he scored his first goal for the club in a 2–1 victory over [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Patel |first=Aadam |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cgmnk4482j3t |title=Liverpool 2–1 Wolverhampton Wanderers |publisher=BBC Sport |date=27 December 2025 }}</ref>

== International career ==
=== Youth ===
Wirtz represented Germany at [[Germany national under-15 football team|under-15]], [[Germany national under-16 football team|under-16]], [[Germany national under-17 football team|under-17]] and [[Germany national under-21 football team|under-21]] levels. While playing for the U21 side at the [[2021 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]], he scored twice in a 2–1 semi-final victory against the [[Netherlands national under-21 football team|Netherlands]] as Germany went on to win the tournament.<ref>{{cite news |date=26 April 2023 |title=13 fun facts about Florian Wirtz |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/lists/13-fun-facts-about-florian-wirtz/blt2b371514166d6401 |access-date=11 August 2025 |publisher=Goal}}</ref>

=== Senior ===
==== 2020–24: Debut and first goals ====
In March 2021, Wirtz received his first call up to the German senior team from manager [[Joachim Löw]] for [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|qualifying]] matches against [[Iceland national football team|Iceland]], [[Romania national football team|Romania]] and [[North Macedonia national football team|North Macedonia]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Start ins EM-Jahr: Musiala und Wirtz erstmals im DFB-Team |url=https://www.dfb.de/news/detail/start-ins-em-jahr-musiala-und-wirtz-erstmals-im-dfb-team-225461/ |publisher=German Football Association |access-date=25 March 2021 |language=de |archive-date=29 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210829095201/https://www.dfb.de/news/detail/start-ins-em-jahr-musiala-und-wirtz-erstmals-im-dfb-team-225461/ |url-status=live}}</ref> He later made his debut on 2 September in another [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group J|World Cup qualifier]] against [[Liechtenstein national football team|Liechtenstein]], coming on as a substitute for [[Joshua Kimmich]] in a 2–0 away victory for the Germans.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Deutschland erfüllt seine Pflicht gegen Liechtenstein |url=https://www.zeit.de/sport/2021-09/wm-qualifikation-deutschland-lichtenstein |website=Die Zeit |date=2 September 2021 |language=de |quote=Kurz vor Schluss kam Toptalent Florian Wirtz und wurde zum ersten Debütanten unter Flick |trans-quote=Shortly before the end, top talent Florian Wirtz arrived and became the first debutant under Flick. |access-date=10 May 2024 |archive-date=10 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240510094652/https://www.zeit.de/sport/2021-09/wm-qualifikation-deutschland-lichtenstein |url-status=live}}</ref>

In May 2022, coach [[Hansi Flick]] expressed his willingness to name Wirtz in the final squad for the 2022 FIFA World Cup, though he ultimately missed the tournament due to his ACL injury.<ref>{{Cite web |title=News in brief: Flick on World Cup chances for Wirtz |url=https://www.bayer04.de/en-us/news/bayer04/news-in-brief-flick-on-world-cup-chances-for-wirtz |website=Bayer 04 Leverkusen |date=20 May 2022 |access-date=27 October 2023 |archive-date=27 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231027120622/https://www.bayer04.de/en-us/news/bayer04/news-in-brief-flick-on-world-cup-chances-for-wirtz |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 23 March 2024, he scored his first senior goal for Germany seven seconds into a friendly match against [[France national football team|France]], a 2–0 away victory, breaking [[Lukas Podolski]]'s record, also becoming the second fastest goalscorer in international football history behind [[Austria national football team|Austrian]] footballer [[Christoph Baumgartner]], who scored a goal in just six seconds in another friendly match against [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]] on the same day.<ref>{{Cite news |title=France 0–2 Germany: Florian Wirtz scores visitors' quickest international goal |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68648714 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=23 March 2023 |access-date=24 March 2023 |archive-date=24 March 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240324005238/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68648714 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Austria striker Christoph Baumgartner scores fastest goal in international football history |url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/sport/350224067/austria-striker-christoph-baumgartner-scores-fastest-goal-international-football#:~:text=Austria%20striker%20Cristoph%20Baumgartner%20scored,in%20their%20match%20against%20France |website=[[Stuff (company)|Stuff]] |date=23 March 2023 |access-date=24 March 2023 |archive-date=24 March 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240324020158/https://www.stuff.co.nz/sport/350224067/austria-striker-christoph-baumgartner-scores-fastest-goal-international-football#:~:text=Austria%20striker%20Cristoph%20Baumgartner%20scored,in%20their%20match%20against%20France. |url-status=live}}</ref>

==== 2024–25: Euros and Nations League ====
On 7 June 2024, Wirtz was named in Germany's squad for [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://olympics.com/en/news/uefa-euro-2024-all-squads-and-players-full-list |title=UEFA Euro 2024: All squads and players full list |date=7 June 2024 |access-date=7 June 2024 |publisher=International Olympic Committee |archive-date=8 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240608183748/https://olympics.com/en/news/uefa-euro-2024-all-squads-and-players-full-list |url-status=live}}</ref> On 14 June, he netted the opener of the tournament in a 5–1 victory over [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]], becoming the youngest German player to score in the [[European Championship]], aged 21 years and 42 days, breaking the previous record set by Kai Havertz.<ref>{{cite web |last=Radnedge |first=Christian |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/kids-are-alright-germanys-new-generation-give-hope-nation-2024-06-14/ |title=The kids are alright – Germany's new generation give hope to a nation |work=Reuters |date=14 June 2024}}</ref> In the [[UEFA Euro 2024 knockout stage#Quarter-finals|quarter-final]] against [[Spain national football team|Spain]], Wirtz replaced [[Leroy Sané]] at half-time and scored an 89th-minute equalising goal which took the match to extra time. Spain went on to win 2–1 with a 119th-minute goal, knocking Germany out of the tournament.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/match/2036205--spain-vs-germany/lineups/ |title=Spain vs Germany: Line-ups |access-date=7 July 2024 |publisher=UEFA}}</ref>

On 7 September 2024, Wirtz made his [[UEFA Nations League]] debut in their opening group match against [[Hungary national football team|Hungary]], scoring a goal and providing an assist in a 5–0 victory.<ref>{{cite news |date=7 September 2024 |title=Germany 5–0 Hungary: Germany thrash Hungary in Nations League opener |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cy9erxvydwqt |access-date=11 August 2025 |publisher=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> On matchday five of the [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League|competition]], he netted the first [[Free kick (association football)|free kick]] of his professional career as he scored a brace in a 7–0 win over [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]].<ref>{{cite news |date=7 September 2024 |title=Germany 7–0 Bosnia-Herzegovina |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cgqyz0xdgg3t |access-date=11 August 2025 |publisher=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> He would eventually top the group stage with his country and qualify for the quarter-finals against [[Italy national football team|Italy]], which he missed due to injury, but which Germany went on to win. In the [[2025 UEFA Nations League Finals#Semi-finals|semi-finals]], he scored to give Germany the lead against [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]], though his side were eventually eliminated from the tournament following a 2–1 defeat.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Portugal 2–1 Germany (Jun 4, 2025) Final Score |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/723735/portugal-germany |access-date=2025-06-11 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref>

==== 2025–26: World Cup season ====
After failing to secure bronze at the [[2025 UEFA Nations League Finals|Nations League]], Wirtz and his country would qualify themselves for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]] in [[United States|USA]], [[Mexico]] and [[Canada]]. During the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|qualifiers]] in late 2025, Wirtz would score a freekick and assist two further goals in six matches.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Florian Wirtz 2026 English Premier League Stats: Goals, Assists & Performance |url=https://tribuna.com/en/persons/florian-wirtz/stat/2026/world-cup-qualification/ |access-date=2026-03-28 |website=Tribuna.com}}</ref>

On 27 March 2026, he'd secure his country the first victory of the year in a pre-tournament friendly in [[Basel]] against [[Switzerland]], with the match ending 3–4. Having been involved in all goals, his two goals and assists were marked by technical quality and composure.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Hornung |first=Christian |title=Deutschland gegen Schweiz: Wirtz weltklasse - nur die DFB-Abwehr macht Sorgen |url=https://www.sportschau.de/fussball/nationalmannschaft/wirtz-weltklasse-nur-die-abwehr-macht-sorgen,spielbericht-schweiz-deutschland-wm-testspiel-104.html |access-date=2026-03-28 |website=sportschau.de |language=de}}</ref> On 21 May 2026, he was selected in Germany’s 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dfb.de/news/bundestrainer-nagelsmann-gibt-wm-kader-bekannt|title=Bundestrainer Nagelsmann gibt WM-Kader bekannt|publisher=[[German Football Association]]|language=de|date=21 May 2026|access-date=21 May 2026}}</ref>

== Player profile ==
Wirtz is a versatile attacking midfielder, although he can also play wide as an inverted [[Winger (football)|winger]]. He was also sometimes used as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] or a [[false nine]] by [[Xabi Alonso]] at [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]]. His outstanding technique helps him to quickly find solutions to set up his teammates while simultaneously having an offensive drive himself. He combines this with a good sense of space and the right pass or cross, but also poses a potent threat himself.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2024-05-20 |title=Fußball-Bundesliga: Offensivstar Wirtz als Spieler der Saison geehrt |url=https://www.spiegel.de/sport/fussball/fussball-bundesliga-florian-wirtz-zum-spieler-der-saison-gewaehlt-a-f890c0f1-f19f-4bf7-bb77-86baa61c198b |access-date=2025-05-28 |work=Der Spiegel |language=de |issn=2195-1349}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=12 January 2021 |title=Wonderkids: Florian Wirtz {{!}} Soccerment Research |url=https://soccerment.com/wonderkids-florian-wirtz/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210304222919/https://soccerment.com/wonderkids-florian-wirtz/ |archive-date=4 March 2021 |access-date=5 February 2021 |website=Soccerment}}</ref> Wirtz has been noted particularly for his off-the-ball movement and high work rate, covering a lot of ground and playing in many areas of the pitch.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bate |first1=Adam |title=Florian Wirtz is Liverpool's running man: Why the Germany international's work rate is just as important as his technique |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/12028/13415669/florian-wirtz-is-liverpools-running-man-why-the-germany-internationals-work-rate-is-just-as-important-as-his-technique |website=Sky Sports |date=25 August 2025}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Wirtz's parents are his agents; his father, Hans-Joachim, is also chairman of [[Grün-Weiß Brauweiler]], the club that Wirtz played for as a child before joining [[1. FC Köln|Köln]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.express.de/sport/fussball/bayer-04-leverkusen/florian-wirtz-sorgt-dank-dfl-fuer-geldsegen-in-brauweiler-77112?cb=1650218428827 |title=8000 Euro für Papa Hätten Sie ihn erkannt? Nationalspieler macht rheinischen Dorfklub froh |website=express.de |language=de |date=20 October 2021 |access-date=17 April 2022 |archive-date=17 April 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220417180756/https://www.express.de/sport/fussball/bayer-04-leverkusen/florian-wirtz-sorgt-dank-dfl-fuer-geldsegen-in-brauweiler-77112?cb=1650218428827 |url-status=live}}</ref> Wirtz has nine siblings, four brothers and five sisters.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Wirtz: Kein Druck, nur Freude am Spiel {{!}} Bayer04.de |url=https://www.bayer04.de/de-de/news/bayer04/wirtz-kein-druck-nur-freude-am-spiel |access-date=2025-05-28 |website=Bayer 04 Leverkusen Fussball GmbH |language=de}}</ref> His older sister [[Juliane Wirtz|Juliane]] is a professional footballer as well.<ref name="Wonderkid" />

Wirtz has been dating model and influencer Aaliyah Cloßen Mohamed since about 2022. The relationship has generated minor controversy given the fact that Cloßen Mohamed is Muslim, while Wirtz is not.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Is Florian Wirtz Muslim? Clearing the Confusion Around His Religion |url=https://www.thickaccent.com/2025/09/14/is-florian-wirtz-muslim-clearing-the-confusion-around-his-religion/ |website=Thick Accent |publisher=Thick Accent |author=Nikhil Kaza |date=14 September 2025 |access-date=25 February 2026}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Who Is Aaliyah Mohamed? Everything About Florian Wirtz Girlfriend |url=https://alleysport.com/who-is-aaliyah-mohamed-everything-about-florian-wirtz-girlfriend/ |website=Alley Sport |publisher=Alley Sport |date=15 August 2025 |access-date=25 February 2026}}</ref>

